TRANSP:OPAQUE
UID:c39ae7c8-e4a3-4078-aaa2-b0326327da8b
DTSTAMP:20250204T053005
SUMMARY:Denise/ Hector- McKinley Elementary Career Day
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20250206T084500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20250206T110000
DESCRIPTION:8:45-9:00am Check in t@ he staff lounge\, schedules\, school
 maps and pastries will be provided.
  Parking- If there are parking spots available in the parking lot you ar
 e welcomed to take them if not street\n
  parking is available.\n
  Assignment-  There will be 3 rotations x 20 min each\n
  & students will come to you.  Please allow a few minutes to answer stud
 ents' questions.\n
  Supplies-You are more than welcome to bring any “tool of the trade”
  that you think would be appropriate and\n
  interesting to represent your profession. Also please let us know if th
 ere are any supplies\, resources needed\n
  that we can provide for you.\n
  PowerPoints/Video/Music/etc.\n
  If you need technology set up please let us know as soon as possible so
  we can assign you to an appropriate\n
  room (showing a PowerPoint presentation\, bringing a short DVD\, etc.).
 \n
  Suggested Talking Points\n
  -What is your job title?\n
  -What do you have to do at your job/what are your duties?\n
  -Why/how did you choose this career?\n
  -What education does someone need to have for your job (high school\, t
 ech school\, college\, graduate degree\,\n
  etc.)?\n
  -What is your favorite part about your job?\n
  -What is the hardest part about your job?\n
  -What things did you learn in elementary school that might help you wit
 h your job today (reading\,\n
  responsibility\, to work collaboratively with others\, perseverance\, h
 ow to solve problems\, etc.)?\n
  -What skills/strength does someone with your career need to have (team
 player\, attention to detail\, good\n
  writer\, some who loves animals\, etc.)?\n
  -What advice would you give a student when choosing this career?\n
  -What attracted you to this job? As a child\, were you interested in th
 is type of work?\n
  \nVENUE INFO:\n
    tel:+1 818-729-2000\n
    https://www.burbankusd.org/wmes\n
  \n*************************************\nSCHEDULE:\n
  8:45 AM - 11:00 AM PST: Program\n  8\;45-9am- Guest check in to Lounge
 and get set up\n
  9:15-9:35- Round 1\n
  9:40-10:00- Round 2\n
  10:00-10:25- Break (pastries /coffee in the library)\n
  10:30-10:50- Round 3\n
  10:50am- Pack up and check out in the lounge\n
  \n----------------------------------------\n
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CLASS:PUBLIC
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.burbankusd.org/wmes
GEO:34.1663956;-118.3104962
LOCATION:McKinley Elementary School\n349 W Valencia Ave\nBurbank CA  9150
 6 United States
