UID:92e01180-f08d-40e1-89dc-ecb13d34aa60
DTSTAMP:20250725T235107
SUMMARY:San Luis Obispo LC CONCERT
DTSTART:20251006T173000Z
DTEND:20251007T005500Z
X-FUNAMBOL-ALLDAY:1
X-MICROSOFT-CDO-ALLDAYEVENT:1
DESCRIPTION:one 30-minute planning Zoom call with OUDI Leadership Team to
  discuss event
  one 1-hour keynote presentation (or panel\, workshop\, etc.) during th
 e symposium\n
  one 1-hour performance  4PM or 5PM show)\n
  one 1-hour meet & greet or meal with student leaders\n
  \nVENUE INFO:\n
    tel:+1 805-756-1111\n
    https://www.calpoly.edu/\n
  \n*************************************\nSCHEDULE:\n
  10:30 AM PDT: 10:30 arrive Cal Poly\n  Cal Poly SLO\n
  1 Grand Ave. San Luis Obispo\, CA\, 93407\n
  ¡Adelante! HSI Symposium – Website\n
  Register your car(s) for parking:\n
  https://www.offstreet.io/events/9RV8SA0T\n
  CODE: HSI\n
  \n----------------------------------------\n
  10:30 AM - 5:55 PM PDT: SLO Day schedule\n  10:30AM BAND MEMBERS ARRIVE
  AT CAL POLY\n
  10:45 AM KEYNOTE CHECK-IN BACKSTAGE\n
  11AM – 12PM KEYNOTE ADDRESS and Q&A\n
  12PM LUNCH & CONCERT SET-UP BEGINS IN UU PLAZA\n
  Lunch Buffet in Chumash Auditorium\n
  12:30pm unload van/ Angie set-up Audio\n
  2 PM SOUND CHECK IN UU PLAZA\n
  4-5 PM CONCERT in UU PLAZA!\n
  5-5:30 PM MERCH SALES & SIGNING at Booth\n
  5:30-6 PM RETURN TO DRESSING ROOMS PACK UP FOR DEPARTURE\n
  \n----------------------------------------\n
  11:00 AM - 11:35 AM PDT: Hector Keynote speech:\n  keynote DETAILS:\n
  TITLE: The Sounds of Resistance: From Storytelling to Movement Building
 \n
  Description: Stories have always been at the heart of resistance. They
  preserve memory\, carry truth across generations\, and spark the imagin
 ation needed to build a different future. This keynote explores how stor
 ytelling can move beyond the personal to fuel collective action and tran
 sformational change. Through words of empowerment\, cultural rhythms\, a
 nd reclaimed narratives\, we will reflect on how stories carve space for
  justice\, belonging\, and possibility.\n
  BULLET POINTS FOR KEYNOTE SPEAKER:\n
  Las Cafeteras introduction: what are the origins of the band\, what ar
 e your art\, culture\, and musical influences.\n
  Local grassroots efforts: talk about Las Cafeteras relationship with th
 eir local community\, share how communities use the creative arts to res
 pond\, resist\, and reimagine social injustice.\n
  Connection to higher education: why it matters for students to develop
 their voices and reclaim their narratives\, how does one begin to practi
 ce storytelling and to be a part of the collective reframing of our stor
 ies.\n
  Movement building through the arts: provide examples of how music\, per
 formance\, and creative expression embody resilience and collective powe
 r\, in what ways does Las Cafeteras create spaces of belonging.\n
  Art as a reminder of hope and possibility: talk about imagination as a
 tool for envisioning new futures\, leave us with a sense of hope and pos
 sibility to continue to take care of our communities while advocating fo
 r a better tomorrow.\n
  \n----------------------------------------\n
  4:00 PM - 5:00 PM PDT: 1 hr Concert\n----------------------------------
 ------\n
  \n*************************************\nACCOMMODATIONS:\n
    Hotel - Best Western Plus Santa Barbara\n
    Santa Barbara\, CA\, 93105\, US\n
    ARRIVE: 10/6/2025 3:00 PM PDT\n
    DEPART: 10/7/2025 11:00 AM PDT\n
    Reservation details\n
  Booked\n
