TRANSP:OPAQUE
UID:147d72fb-b66f-4805-af3b-759a47e914a8
DTSTAMP:20250102T072028
SUMMARY:HLM Youth Show
DTSTART:20251007T144000Z
DTEND:20251008T033000Z
X-FUNAMBOL-ALLDAY:1
X-MICROSOFT-CDO-ALLDAYEVENT:1
DESCRIPTION:CONTACT: LYNDSEY
  lyndsay@sbbowl.com\n
  K-12\n
  Kids at the Bowl\, 60 minute set + an additional\, smaller-scale outrea
 ch opportunity to a select group of attending students. We would host th
 is outreach activity after the concert – either at the Bowl or possibl
 y at a nearby school site.\n
  2\,700 students registered from more than 20 schools across the county!
  The students are in grades 7–12\, which means the age range is approx
 imately 12 to 18 years.\n
  A description of the Viva Los Muertos youth show (60-min performance\
 , 2\,500+ students)\n
  A description of the post-show workshop (60-min workshop\, 25 students)
 \n
  \nVENUE INFO:\n
    tel:+1 805-962-7411\n
    http://www.sbbowl.com/\n
  \n*************************************\nSCHEDULE:\n
  7:40 AM PDT: Call time at your vehicle (check out hotel)\n-------------
 ---------------------------\n
  8:00 AM PDT: LC Load-in/ soundcheck (dancers block)\n------------------
 ----------------------\n
  10:00 AM PDT: Doors\n----------------------------------------\n
  11:00 AM - 12:00 PM PDT: SHOWTIME! 60 min\n----------------------------
 ------------\n
  12:00 PM - 12:45 PM PDT: Lunch\n---------------------------------------
 -\n
  12:45 PM - 1:45 PM PDT: Workshop (1 hr): Art of Remembering\n  Art of R
 emembering\n
  “To know who you are\, you must know who you were.” In the spirit o
 f Dia de Los Muertos\, we will engage participants in the sacred practic
 e of remembering. Through storytelling exercises\, poetry prompts and c
 ollective sharing\, we will guide students to understand the Power of yo
 ur past to forge your future.\n
  I am From writing exercise\n
  I am from\n
  I dream of\n
  I fear\n
  One day I will\n
  I will be remembered as\n
  Themes:\n
  Stories are powerful\n
  legacy\n
  culture\n
  this is how we remember\n
  \n----------------------------------------\n
  3:30 PM - 8:30 PM PDT: Drive out to Merced\, CA (5 hours)\n------------
 ----------------------------\n
