SUMMARY:NEW YORK- APAP SHOWCASE (Alih confirmed)
DTSTART:20260110T163000Z
DTEND:20260111T040000Z
X-FUNAMBOL-ALLDAY:1
X-MICROSOFT-CDO-ALLDAYEVENT:1
DESCRIPTION:LOAD-IN
  If you have a lot of gear to load-in\, you can unload before parking yo
 ur vehicle and then circle back around to park. There is an alley gate j
 ust north of the main Public Theater steps on Lafayette Street (on the r
 ight just past the steps if you are driving up Lafayette) where you can
 unload. Depending on how much equipment you have\, you can either come i
 n through the lobby (there is a ramp) or the alley (there is a lift). Yo
 u can call once you've arrived\, and our crew can come out and meet you
 with an empty cart. Our crew can help you get gear backstage and then yo
 u can go park your vehicle.\n
  INSTRUCTIONS FOR ENTRY/STICKERS\n
  Everyone working onsite must enter through the front of the Public Thea
 ter (425 Lafayette). Please have your group check in with security/front
  desk. They will give you a sticker on arrival and call for our performa
 nce team to come get you. After receiving your sticker\, you will be bro
 ught inside of Joe’s Pub. While onsite\, please always wear or carry y
 our sticker.\n
  FOOD & BEVERAGE\n
  The Joe’s Pub performance coordinator for the evening will provide yo
 u with drink tickets (1 per performer)\, coffee & tea\, small snacks\, a
 nd towels – all upon request. Food is available to order backstage fro
 m our Joe’s Pub menu for 50% off. If this is of interest\, please ask
 for a menu from the performance coordinator on the night of show.\n
  As part of the Public Theater’s institutional efforts to create a ‘
 greener’ venue\, please note that Joe’s Pub does not provide bottled
  water. Unlimited hot/cold filtered water is available from the cooler i
 n your dressing room: we encourage you to use the glassware provided o
 r bring your own reusable (and closeable) drinking vessel.\n
  MERCH\n
  If you are planning on selling merchandise\, you may do so after your
  performance and you must provide your own seller. Your merch setup will
  be located outside of the entrance to Joe’s Pub inside The Public T
 heater lobby. Please let us know in advance if you decide to sell merch
 and we will assist in setting up a 6-foot table with a black tablecloth.
  We do not take any percentage of the merch sales.\n
  \nVENUE INFO:\n
    tel:+1 212-539-8778\n
    http://www.joespub.com/\n
  \n*************************************\nSCHEDULE:\n
  11:30 AM - 2:30 PM EST: Load-in & Sound Check (2hrs MAX)\n  PLEASE NOTE
 : there is another show before yours\, so you will need to strike all yo
 ur gear and clear the stage after your sound check. You will be able to
 reset the stage and do a quick line check before doors open for your sho
 w.\n
  LOAD-IN\n
  If you have a lot of gear to load-in\, you can unload before parking yo
 ur vehicle and then circle back around to park. There is an alley gate j
 ust north of the main Public Theater steps on Lafayette Street (on the r
 ight just past the steps if you are driving up Lafayette) where you can
 unload.\n
  Depending on how much equipment you have\, you can either come in throu
 gh the lobby (there is a ramp) or the alley (there is a lift). You can c
 all once you've arrived\, and our crew can come out and meet you with an
  empty cart. Our crew can help you get gear backstage and then you can g
 o park your vehicle.\n
  INSTRUCTIONS FOR ENTRY/STICKERS\n
  Everyone working onsite must enter through the front of the Public Thea
 ter (425 Lafayette). Please have your group check in with security/front
  desk. They will give you a sticker on arrival and call for our performa
 nce team to come get you. After receiving your sticker\, you will be bro
 ught inside of Joe’s Pub. While onsite\, please always wear or carry y
 our sticker.\n
  \n----------------------------------------\n
  7:45 PM - 8:00 PM EST: Call-time (Dressed for show)\n------------------
 ----------------------\n
  8:30 PM EST: Stage re-set\n----------------------------------------\n
  9:00 PM EST: DOORS\n----------------------------------------\n
  9:30 PM - 11:00 PM EST: SHOWTIME! 90 min\n-----------------------------
 -----------\n
  11:00 PM EST: Curfew\n----------------------------------------\n
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CLASS:PUBLIC
