SUMMARY:New Orleans- Folk Alliance
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260121
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260127
X-FUNAMBOL-ALLDAY:1
X-MICROSOFT-CDO-ALLDAYEVENT:1
DESCRIPTION:Backline Provided:
  The Waterbury room has the following inventory and backline provided:\n
  Drum Kit\, sponsored by Treehouse Drums\, with all hardware and cymbal
 s (bring your own sticks/brushes). Drum kit sizes vary and are sized app
 ropriately to match the room size\n
  Bass Amp provided by sponsor Phil Jones Bass\, exact model will vary b
 ased on room size\n
  Two Guitar Amps (Boss KTN-50\, KTN-100\, or KTN-212) provided by spo
 nsor Roland\, the exact model of amplifier varies based on room size.\n
  Roland RD-08 88-key weighted stage piano w/ stand\, pedal\, & bench\,
 provided by sponsor Roland\n
  Music stands\, small tables\, stools\, and chairs are available as requ
 ested in stage plots\n
  Any backline items not listed above that are required for your showcase
  are the responsibility of the artist to provide.\n
  \nVENUE INFO:\n
    tel:+1 504-525-2500\n
    https://www.marriott.com/en-us/hotels/msyis-sheraton-new-orleans-hote
 l/overview/?scid=f2ae0541-1279-4f24-b197-a979c79310b0\n
  \n*************************************\nSCHEDULE:\n
  1/23/2026 1:00 PM - 1/23/2026 3:00 PM CST: Denis and Hector on Panel: C
 ross Cultural Call to Coalition. Neat. NO ICE.\n  Fri 23 Jan\n
  1:30 PM to 2:30 PM\n
  A Cross Cultural Call to Coalition. Neat. NO ICE.\n
  Show Stage/Venue Maurepas - Floor 3\n
  A Cross Cultural Call to Coalition. Neat. NO ICE.\n
  "Calling All Comrades\, Cajuns\, Creoles\,\n
  and Chicanas/Chicanos! Join members of Las Cafeteras\, Lost Bayou RamBe
 ltsand Leyla McCalla for a powerful conversation on solidarithmetic\, th
 e interconnectedness of liberation movements\, and how our communities c
 an resist the rise of fascism. Hoodyhoo! It’s an all-hands-on-deck mom
 ent - and time to rise up! Together\,we’ll share strategies\, ideas\,\
 n
  and visions for how to support\, uplift\,and\n
  protect one another across lines of culture\, identity\,and geography.\
 n
  ﻿\n
  Moderated by Kara St. Clair\, this session promises plenty of laughs\,
 real talk\,anda deep sense of collective purpose.\n
  \n----------------------------------------\n
  1/24/2026 12:45 PM - 1/24/2026 2:30 PM CST: Hector on panel: Climate Cr
 isis and Social Justice\n  Saturday\, January 24th\, at 1pm.\n
  Arrive 12:45\n
  "How Artists Can Be Force Multipliers in Addressing the Climate Crisis
 and Social Justice"\n
  . We want panelists to draw on a broad array of experiences to share ap
 proaches and lessons learned around using music for activism. We'll also
  be sharing information in the panel about a global fan engagement and c
 limate action model we've been developing that would make it easier for
 artists to connect their fans with organizations curated to align with t
 heir values and maximize impact.\n
  \n----------------------------------------\n
  1/24/2026 3:00 PM CST: 3pm Lobby time- bring all gear for show\n-------
 ---------------------------------\n
  1/24/2026 4:00 PM CST: Load-in & set up  Gear/ ALL HANDS ON DECK\n-----
 -----------------------------------\n
  1/24/2026 8:00 PM - 1/24/2026 10:00 PM CST: LC SHOWCASE (ARRIVE DRESSED
  TO PERFORM)- Waterbury - Floor 2\n  8pm call time\n
  8:45pm  changeover (15 min)\n
  9:20-9:45pm show time (25min\n
  \n----------------------------------------\n
  1/25/2026 12:30 AM CST: 1am Saturday showcase\n  Room 1030 / FLi Livin
 g Traditions Room\n
  1am Sat nite CLoSInG PARTY SHOWCASE!!!\n
  \n----------------------------------------\n
